This suggests a strong connection to the field of cybersecurity and digital forensics, which falls under the cs.CR sub-category.

- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper may also be relevant to the field of distributed computing, as it deals with the analysis of data remnants from the use of instant messaging apps on a Windows client machine. This could involve issues related to data storage, retrieval, and processing, which are common topics in the cs.DC sub-category.

- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper may also have implications for the study of the social and ethical aspects of instant messaging, as it deals with the potential risks and benefits of using such apps for communication. This could involve issues related to privacy, security, and user behavior, which are common topics in the cs.CY sub-category.

- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper may also be relevant to the field of human-computer interaction, as it deals with the user experience of using instant messaging apps on a Windows client machine.
